      • ROConnector

        public ROConnector(JMXServiceURL url,
                   Map<String,?> environment)

        Constructs an ROConnector that will connect the RO connector server with the given address.

        Parameters:
        url - the address of the RO connector server.
        environment - additional attributes specifying how to make the connection. This parameter can be null, which is equivalent to an empty Map.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if url is null.

      • ROConnector

        public ROConnector(ROServerImpl roServer,
                   Map<String,?> environment)

        Constructs an ROConnector using the given RO server stub.

        Parameters:
        roServer - a RO stub representing the RO connector server.
        environment - additional attributes specifying how to make the connection. This parameter can be null, which is equivalent to an empty Map.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if roServer is null.
